## What is Node.js?

Node.js is a cross-platform runtime environment for executing java script code outside of a browser.</br>
It is used to build highly scalable, data -intensive & real time apps. It is also used to build backend services API (Application Programming Interfaces)

What's so special about Node.js?

* Great for prototyping and agile development
* Superfast and highly scalable
* Cleaner & consistent codebase
* Open Source
